When I'm trying to get the identity info from a GxsId extracted from getIdentitiesSummaries, sometimes I get a broken JSON object.

Example:

```json
{
    "idsInfo": [
        {
            "mMeta": {
                "mGroupId": "XXXXXXXX",
                "mGroupName": "XXXXX",
                "mGroupFlags": 257,
                "mSignFlags": 0,
                "mPublishTs": {
                    "xint64": 1589714816,
                    "xstr64": "1589714816"
                },
                "mAuthorId": "00000000000000000000000000000000",
                "mCircleId": "00000000000000000000000000000000",
                "mCircleType": 1,
                "mAuthenFlags": 0,
                "mParentGrpId": "00000000000000000000000000000000",
                "mSubscribeFlags": 4,
                "mPop": 0,
                "mVisibleMsgCount": 0,
                "mLastPost": {
                    "xint64": 0,
                    "xstr64": "0"
                },
                "mGroupStatus": 768,
                "mServiceString": "v2 {P:K:0 T:1624262356 C:4 I:3B847C62F1DB4A42}{T:F:4096 P:1589714816 T:1623163556}{R:20 20 0 0}",
                "mOriginator": "XXXXXXX",
                "mInternalCircle": "00000000000000000000000000000000"
            },
            "mPgpIdHash": "XXXXXXXXXXX",
            "mPgpIdSign": "��\\\u0004\u0000\u0001\u0002\u0000\u0010\u0005\u0002^�\u001F\t\u0010;�|b��JB\u0000\u0000��\u0007�#ġ4\u0006\u001EB�E7rc�/Ւ��̀�Wp���|\u001B�u��\u0019�#Q�ho��K�\ff�|�,\"\u0005�Y���\u001F��Xk��l\u001D���W���7\f>H�\u0012�\u0017�\u0018\u0007\"ꪗ����;�̊��9��i��#b���t�\u0005ٳ�x\u0012�h�l&%                                
```

This cause the impossibility to parse de JSON.  I created a script to try to check when it happen:

```bash
#/bin/bash

curl -u "test:test" http://127.0.0.1:9092/rsIdentity/getIdentitiesSummaries |  jq -r  '.ids[] | .mGroupId ' > tmp

for n in $(cat tmp )
do
    curl -u "test:test"  -d '{ "ids" : ["'$n'"] }' http://127.0.0.1:9092/rsIdentity/getIdentitiesInfo
done
```

It seem that `mPgpIdSign` is not well serialized. 

Also, a test for dart, using elrepo-lib:

```dart
test("testFollowAPI", () async {
      AUTH.initLocal();
      print("Result");
      // print(await repo.getFollowedAuthorsInfo());
      var ids = await rs.RsIdentity.getIdentitiesSummaries();
      var idsError = [];
      for(var id in ids) {
        try {
          print(await rs.RsIdentity.getIdentitiesInfo([id["mGroupId"]]));
        } catch (e){
          print(e)
          print("error for identity $id");
          idsError.add(id);
        }
      }
      print("total ids ${ids.length}");
      print("total errors ${idsError.length}");
    });
```

The resulting error on dart is: 

```
FormatException: Missing extension byte (at offset 1271)
```

The quantity of errors on Dart seem much bigger than on bash, or also, on bash piping to seem `jq`  less more.

